{% extends 'emails/onboarding/onboarding_email_base.html.twig' %}

{% block preheader %}
    Eliminate email attachments and complex client portals starting today.
{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
    <row class="content-body">
        <columns>
            <h2>Welcome to FileDrop Pro!</h2>

            <p>Dear {{ recipient_name }},</p>

            <p>We are thrilled to help your firm streamline secure document collection while keeping your client data locked behind a mathematical, zero-knowledge firewall.</p>

            <div class="trial-callout">
                🚀 You are currently running on a <strong>14-day free trial of our fully featured Pro Plan</strong> (expires on {{ trial_end_date }}).
            </div>

            <p>Unlike standard cloud sync tools, FileDrop Pro was built with a single guiding principle: <strong>Security shouldn't cause client friction.</strong></p>

            <p>Your clients don't want to register accounts, remember usernames, or handle password reset prompts just to send you a sensitive PDF. With FileDrop Pro, they don't have to.</p>

            <!-- Setup Card -->
            <div class="step-block">
                <h3>Get Started: Send a drop link to a client</h3>
                <p>To start collecting secure files immediately, send drop link invitations to your clients:</p>
                <ol>
                    <li>Log in to <a href="{{ login_url }}"><strong>FileDrop Pro</strong></a>.</li>
                    <li>Click on <strong>Client Drop Requests</strong> on the top menu.</li>
                    <li>Click on <strong>Invite External Clients to Upload Files</strong>.</li>
                    <li>Wait for your client securely upload one or more files.</li>
                    <li>View the uploaded files by clicking <strong>Documents</strong> on the top menu.</li>
                </ol>
            </div>

            <p>Any file your clients drop onto this link is automatically encrypted <strong>locally in their web browser</strong> using AES-GCM-256 before uploading directly to your secure, compliant cloud partition.</p>

            <spacer size="16"></spacer>

            <button href="{{ login_url }}" class="btn-cta">
                Log In Now
            </button>
        </columns>
    </row>
{% endblock %}
